### Fetch All Bookings - useBookings Hook

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/docs/platform/bookings-hooks.mdx

The useBookings hook retrieves an array of bookings for a given user based on their access token. It supports filtering by status, event type ID, and attendee email. The hook returns loading state and booking data. It's intended for platform customers.

```javascript
import { useBookings } from "@calcom/atoms";

export default function Bookings() {
  const { isLoading: isLoadingUpcomingBookings, data: upcomingBookings } = useBookings({
    take: 50,
    skip: 0,
    status: ["upcoming"],
  });

  return (
    <>
      <h1>Upcoming bookings</h1>
      {isLoadingUpcomingBookings && <p>Loading...</p>}
      {!isLoadingUpcomingBookings && !upcomingBookings && <p>No upcoming bookings found</p>}
      {!isLoading &&
        upcomingBookings &&
        (Boolean(upcomingBookings?.length)) &&
        [...upcomingBookings].map((booking) => {
            return (
                <div key={booking.id}><h1>{booking.title}</h1></div>
            );
       })}
    </>
  );
}
```

