### Reschedule a Booking

Source: https://context7.com/calcom/cal.com/llms.txt

Allows rescheduling an existing booking to a new time slot. Supports both normal and seated bookings.

```APIDOC
## POST /v2/bookings/{bookingId}/reschedule

### Description
Reschedules an existing booking to a new time slot. Supports both normal and seated bookings.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
`/v2/bookings/{bookingId}/reschedule`

### Path Parameters
- **bookingId** (string) - Required - The ID of the booking to reschedule.

### Request Body
- **start** (string) - Required - The new start time for the booking in ISO 8601 format.
- **reschedulingReason** (string) - Optional - The reason for rescheduling.
- **seatUid** (string) - Optional - The UID of the specific seat to reschedule if it's a seated booking.

### Request Example
```json
{
  "start": "2024-01-16T14:00:00Z",
  "reschedulingReason": "Conflict with another meeting"
}
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **status** (string) - Indicates the status of the operation (e.g., "success").
- **data** (object) - Contains the details of the rescheduled booking.
  - **id** (number) - The internal ID of the booking.
  - **uid** (string) - The unique identifier for the booking.
  - **title** (string) - The title of the booking.
  - **status** (string) - The current status of the booking (e.g., "accepted").
  - **start** (string) - The new start time of the booking.
  - **end** (string) - The new end time of the booking.
  - **hosts** (array) - Information about the hosts.
  - **attendees** (array) - Information about the attendees.

#### Response Example
```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "data": {
    "id": 789,
    "uid": "bk_new789xyz",
    "title": "30 Min Meeting",
    "status": "accepted",
    "start": "2024-01-16T14:00:00.000Z",
    "end": "2024-01-16T14:30:00.000Z",
    "hosts": [
      {
        "id": 1,
        "name": "Alice Smith",
        "email": "alice@example.com"
      }
    ],
    "attendees": [
      {
        "name": "John Doe",
        "email": "john@example.com"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```
```

