### Cancel Booking - useCancelBooking Hook

Source: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/docs/platform/bookings-hooks.mdx

The useCancelBooking hook provides a mutation function to cancel a booking. It requires the booking's unique identifier (uid) and optionally accepts `cancellationReason` and `allRemainingBookings` for enhanced control. Callbacks for success and error are supported. This hook is for platform customers.

```javascript
import { useCancelBooking } from "@calcom/atoms";

export default function CancelBooking() {
    const { mutate: cancelBooking } = useCancelBooking({
    onSuccess: () => {
      console.log("Booking canceled successfully!")
    },
  });

  return (
    <>
      <button onClick={() => {
          cancelBooking({
            uid: "6L6ADNpVHwLX25V8wXKsBr",
            cancellationReason: "User request",
            allRemainingBookings: true,
          })
        }}>
        Cancel booking
      </button>
    </>
  );
}
```
